FBIS4-38222 "drnes125_s_94010" FBIS-NES-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 Iran Attorney General Rejects Alleged Rights Abuses Attorney General Rejects Alleged Rights Abuses LD2806144594 Tehran IRNA in English 1417 GMT 28 Jun 94 LD2806144594 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, June 28, IRNA -- No one has gone on trial for expressing his thoughts and ideas in the Islamic Republic of Iran, Iran's Attorney General Ayatollah Seyyed Abolfazl Musavi-Tabrizi reiterated here Tuesday [28 June]. Calling as fabricated the claims on human rights violation by certain international circles Musavi-Tabrizi declared that the most progressive types of human rights were present in the Islamic Republic of Iran. Addressing the concluding session of the nationwide seminar on judiciary week, Musavi-Tabrizi said that the Islamic system will not put aside due punishment as decreed by Islam for criminals.
